gurmukhi: srqw brinn Awid aucrIAY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd frIAY ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur bKwno ]nwm qupk ky sB pihcwno ]830]
transliteration: Sartaa Barnin Aadh Udareeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Paddareeai|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bakhaano|| Naam Toupak Ke Sabh Paihchaano||830||
translation: Add the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” after firstly saying the word “Saritaavarni” and recognize all the names of Tupak.830.

gurmukhi: srqyNdRinn Awid aucwro ]jwcr kih piq dY fwro ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur bKwno ]nwm qupk ky sB jIA jwno ]831]
transliteration: Sartendranin Aadh Oucdaro|| Jaachar Kah(i) Pat(i) Pad Dai Daro|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bakhaano|| Naam Toupak Ke Sabh Jeea Jaano||831||
translation: Add the words “Jaachar-pati-shatru” after firstly uttering the word “Saritendrani” and know the names of Tupak in your mind.831.

gurmukhi: srqw niRpinn bkqR qy piRQmY kro aucwr ]jwcr piq kih S`qRu kih nwm qupk jIA Dwr ]832]
transliteration: Sartaa Nripnin Baktra Te Prithmai Daro Ouchaar|| Jaachar Pat(i) Kah(i) Shattru Kah(i) Naam Toupak Teea Dhaar||832||
translation: Utter firstly the word “Saritaanrapnin” from your mouth and then saying the words “Jaachar-pati-shatru”, know the names of Tupak in your mind.832.

gurmukhi: Awid qrMgin rwjin Sbd aucwrIAY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd pun dY fwrIAY ]S`qRu Sbd ko qwky AMq bKwnIAY ]ho skl qupk ky nwm pRbIn pCwnIAY ]833]
transliteration: Aadh Taranad(i) Raajan(i) Shabad Oucdareeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Poundai Dareeai|| Shattru Shabad Kko Taake Ant Bakhaaneeai|| Ho Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Prabeen Pachhaadeeai||833||
translation: Saying firstly the word “Tarang-raajni” and then adding the words “Jaachar-nayak and shatru” at the end, O skilful people ! know all the names of Tupak.833.

gurmukhi: ndI niRpnnI muK qy Awid bKwnIAY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd bhur pRmwnIAY ]S``qRu Sbd ko qwky AMq aucwrIAY ]ho skl qupk ky nwm cqur icq DwrIAY ]834]
transliteration: Naadinripanimoukh Te Aadh Bakhaaneeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Bahur Pramaaneeai|| Shattru Shabad Ko Taake Ant Oucdareeai|| Ho Sakal Toupak Ke Naam Chatur Chit Ddareeai||834||
translation: Utter the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” after firstly saying the word “Nadi-nrapni” and in this way, adopt all the names of Tupak in your mind.834.

gurmukhi: Awid jmunnI Sbd aucwro ]jwcr kih nwiek pd fwro ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur Bix`jY ]nwm quPMg cIn icq il`jY ]835]
transliteration: Aadh Jamounndnishabad Oucdaro|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Daro|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bhanijjai|| Naam Touphan Cheen Chit Lijjai||835||
translation: Utter the word “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” after firstly saying the word “Yamunani” and recognize the names of Tupak in you mind.835.

gurmukhi: kwilMdRnnI Awid aucrIAY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd frIAY ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur bKwno ]sB sRI nwm qupk ky jwno ]836]
transliteration: Kaalindrananiaadh Udareeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Paddareeai|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bakhaano|| Sabh Srinaam Toupak Ke Jaano||836||
translation: Utter the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” after firstly saying the word “Kaalindri” and comprehend all the names of Tupak.836.

gurmukhi: ikSn b`liBn Awid Bix`jY ]jwcr kih nwiek pd id`jY ]S`qRu Sbd ko bhur bKwnIAY ]sB sRI nwm qupk ky jwnIAY ]837]
transliteration: Kishan Ballabhin Aadh Bhanijjai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Deejjai|| Shattru Shabad Ko Bahur Bakhaaneeai|| Sabh Srinaam Toupak Ke Jaaneeai||837||
translation: Utter the words “Jaachar-nayak-shatru” after firstly saying the word “Krishan-ball-bhanani”, and know all the names of Tupak.837.

gurmukhi: bsudyvj b`lBnin BwKo ]jwcr kih nwiek pd rwKo ]sB sRI nwm qupk ky jwno ]Xw mY Byd eyk nhI mwno ]838]
transliteration: Basudevaj Ballbhanin Bhaakho|| Jaachar Kah(i) Naaik Pad Raakho|| Sabh Srinaam Toupak Ke Jaano|| Yaa Mai Bhed Ek Nahimaano||838||
translation: Add the words “Jaachar nayak” after firstly uttering the word “Vasudevaj-vallabhni”, and know all the names of Tupak without any dispute.838.

gurmukhi: skl nwm bsuidv ky Awid aucwrIAY ]jwb`lBnI qw pwCY pd fwrIAY ]jwcr kih irp Sbd bhur iqh BwKIAY ]ho cIn qupk ky nwm cqur icq rwKIAY ]839]
transliteration: Sakal Naam Basudiv Ke Aadh Oucdareeai|| Jaaballabhnitaa Paachhai Pad Dareeai|| Jaachar Kah(i) Rip Shabad Bahur Tih Bhaakheeai|| Ho Cheen Toupak Ke Naam Chatur Chit Raakheeai||839||
translation: Saying firstly all the names of “Vasudev”, and then adding the words “Jaa Vallabhni” and afterwards add the words “Jaachar” and “Ripu”, and recognize cleverly the names of Tupak.839.
